text: Kushulevo () is a rural locality (a selo) in Takarlikovsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 407 as of 2010. There are 15 streets. == Geography == It is located 8 km from Dyurtyuli, 6 km from Ivanayevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Kushulevo
